Mass Media: This is a means of communication that reaches
a large number of people spread over different areas.
Examples are:
Radio
Television
Newspapers
Postal Services: These are services of sending letters and

Registered Mail
Express Mail

Poste Restante

e) Choice of appropriate means of communication
The teacher should guide the learner in discussing factors that
influence choice of an appropriate means of communication. For
example:
• Urgency of the message: When a message is urgent the
most appropriate means of communication should be
selected i.e. telephone. Alternatively, if the message is not
urgent, any other means can be used.
• Cost of the means
• Confidentiality of the means
f) Barriers to effective communication
The teacher should involve the learner in explaining barriers to
effective communication. For example:
• Noise disrupts effective communication.
Telecommunication Services: This refers to communication
over along distance using telephone and telegraph. It can be
done using cable or wireless network.
h) Trends in communication
The teacher should involve the learner in discussing the trends in
communication. These include:
• Facsimile (fax)
